@startuml 04-unlock-lock-flow
title Unlock / Lock / Auto-Lock Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    BorderColor #1976D2
}

state "Locked" as locked #FFCDD2 {
    state "Awaiting Password" as await
}

state "Unlocking" as unlocking #FFF3E0 {
    state "Derive Master KEK" as derive
    state "Unwrap Device Keys" as unwrap
    state "Load Vault from IDB" as loadLocal
    state "Decrypt Vault" as decrypt
    state "Check Remote (Optional)" as checkRemote
}

state "Unlocked" as unlocked #E8F5E9 {
    state "Vault in Memory" as inMemory
    state "Auto-Lock Timer Active" as timer
}

state "Locking" as locking #FFCDD2 {
    state "secureWipe(VaultKey)" as wipeKey
    state "Clear Decrypted Data" as clearData
    state "Reset UI State" as resetUI
}

[*] --> locked

locked --> unlocking : User enters password
await --> derive

derive --> unwrap : KEK derived
unwrap --> loadLocal : Device keys ready
loadLocal --> decrypt : Vault loaded
decrypt --> checkRemote : Vault decrypted

unlocking --> locked : Wrong password\n(decrypt fails)
unlocking --> unlocked : Success

checkRemote --> inMemory : Vault ready

unlocked --> locking : User clicks Lock
unlocked --> locking : Auto-lock timeout\n(default: 5 min)
unlocked --> locking : Browser idle
unlocked --> locking : Extension suspended

inMemory --> timer : Start timer
timer --> wipeKey : Timer expires

wipeKey --> clearData
clearData --> resetUI
locking --> locked

note right of wipeKey
    **Critical Memory Hygiene:**
    - vaultKey.fill(0)
    - passwordBuffer.fill(0)
    - Set references to null
    - Clear all Uint8Arrays
end note

note right of timer
    **Auto-Lock Triggers:**
    - Inactivity timeout (configurable)
    - System idle detection
    - Tab/window blur (optional)
    - Extension suspend event
end note

note bottom of checkRemote
    **Rollback Detection:**
    If remote.timestamp < local.lastSeen:
    Warn user of potential replay attack
end note

@enduml
